s_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "astrocyte", "obj": "cell_type", "prob": 0.6272231936454773, "span": {"begin": 763, "end": 772}}, {"id": ["mesh:D020078"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "chronical neuroinflammation", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.9999672770500183, "span": {"begin": 899, "end": 926}}, {"id": ["mesh:D009410"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "neurodegeneration", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.999998927116394, "span": {"begin": 931, "end": 948}}, {"id": ["mesh:D020078"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "neuroinflammation", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.9997842907905579, "span": {"begin": 999, "end": 1016}}, {"id": ["NCBITaxon:9606"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "patients", "obj": "species", "prob": 0.9766120314598083, "span": {"begin": 1038, "end": 1046}}, {"id": ["mesh:C037850"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "[11C] (R)-PK11195", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9993858337402344, "span": {"begin": 1099, "end": 1116}}, {"id": ["mesh:D000544", "mim:104300"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "sporadic Alzheimer&#39;s disease", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.9659557342529297, "span": {"begin": 1196, "end": 1228}}, {"id": ["mesh:D020078"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "neuroinflammation", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.9923918843269348, "span": {"begin": 1288, "end": 1305}}, {"id": ["mesh:D000544", "mim:104300"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "Alzheimer&#39;s disease", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.999825656414032, "span": {"begin": 1309, "end": 1332}}, {"id": ["CL:0002629"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "activated microglia", "obj": "cell_type", "prob": 0.7691270112991333, "span": {"begin": 1426, "end": 1445}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "astrocytes", "obj": "cell_type", "prob": 0.7711204886436462, "span": {"begin": 1450, "end": 1460}}, {"id": ["mesh:D000544", "mim:104300"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "Alzheimer&#39;s", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.9345204830169678, "span": {"begin": 1490, "end": 1505}}], "text": "Neuroinflammation is a component of neurodegenerative diseases such as Alzheimer&rsquo;s and Parkinson&rsquo;s disease (Neumann, 2001) which may play a secondary or an active primary role in the disease process (Hirsch and Hunot, 2009). McNaull and coworkers (McNaull et al., 2010) suggested that early developmental onset of brain inflammation could be linked with late onset of Alzheimer&rsquo;s disease. A recent paper by Krstic and coworkers (2012) showed that a systemic immune challenge during late gestation predispose mice to develop Alzheimer&rsquo;s like pathology when aging, suggesting a causal link between systemic inflammation, neuroinflammation, and the onset of Alzheimer&rsquo;s disease. Regarding toxicant-induced neuroinflammation, microglial/astrocyte activation and chronic neuron damage may continue for years after initial exposure (Taetsch and Block, 2013), suggesting that chronical neuroinflammation and neurodegeneration have a slow long-term temporal evolution. Ongoing neuroinflammation can be visualized in patients using the positron emission tomography (PET) ligand [11C] (R)-PK11195 (Cagnin et al., 2001). Recent genome-wide association study (GWAS) analyses of sporadic Alzheimer&#39;s disease revealed a set of genes that point to a pathogenic role of neuroinflammation in Alzheimer&#39;s disease (for review, see Heneka et al., 2014). High levels of pro-inflammatory cytokines produced by activated microglia and astrocytes are detected in the brain of Alzheimer&#39;s subjects and animal models (McGeer and McGeer, 1998; Janelsins et al., 2005).&nbsp;", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 14:25:36 +0000 2026"}